column5: For the guys who own property up in Canada, or are knowledgable in that area. How much do you think it costs for a house right on Lac Seul or the river system? We saw some really nice houses on the river going to Gold Pines from Ear Falls.....just wondering what a ballpark price on those would be? Thanks.
Wooglin, I can not speek for that end, however, houses on Pelican which is on the west end start in the low 300's.

One of those homes that you saw was on the market for 250-300,00. If I recall, the taxes were like 9,000 a year.

Pelican is the lake on the west side of sioux lookout. It is on the english river system and I believe it has the last privatly owned land before you get to lac seul. Several lodge owners on lac seul run their guests via boat from pelican.
